        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "X-linked intellectual disability-retinitis pigmentosa syndrome is characterized by moderate intellectual deficit and severe early-onset retinitis pigmentosa. It has been described in five males spanning three generations of one family. Some patients also had microcephaly. It is transmitted as an X-linked recessive trait."
        },
